#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/taylor_green.rst:2
#: a412cf285c544f549f023ad9a1030714
msgid "Taylor-Green Vortex (Convergence Study)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/taylor_green.rst:4
#: 1d01c5fda48740338fae5cc8d1619222
msgid ""
"The Taylor-Green vortex is the canonical incompressible-flow benchmark "
"with a known exact solution: a periodic decaying vortex on the square "
":math:`[0, 2\\pi]^2` whose velocity and pressure can be written down in "
"closed form. The script ``examples/fluid/taylor_green/taylor_green.py`` "
"uses it to drive a quantitative **h-convergence study** of the transient "
"Navier-Stokes solver — the only example in :doc:`index` whose purpose is "
"verification rather than visualization."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/taylor_green.rst:15
#: 791f7b895d924109b37faacfb34faddb
msgid "Exact solution"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/taylor_green.rst:17
#: 2217cb73d1b542a88f2fe37c73328973
msgid "For viscosity :math:`\\nu` and time :math:`t`,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/taylor_green.rst:19
#: d1c022822aa34417985451c42279f52e
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"u(x, y, t) &= -\\cos(x)\\, \\sin(y)\\, e^{-2\\nu t}, \\\\\n"
"v(x, y, t) &= \\phantom{-}\\sin(x)\\, \\cos(y)\\, e^{-2\\nu t}, \\\\\n"
"p(x, y, t) &= -\\tfrac14 \\bigl(\\cos(2x) + \\cos(2y)\\bigr)\\, e^{-4\\nu"
" t}."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/taylor_green.rst:25
#: 08d9fa745c384a008b4c8e94adf35f51
msgid ""
"The velocity decays exponentially with rate :math:`2\\nu` (twice the "
"kinematic viscosity); the pressure decays at rate :math:`4\\nu`. "
"Substitution verifies that :math:`(u, v, p)` satisfies the incompressible"
" Navier-Stokes equations exactly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/taylor_green.rst:31
#: 9889eab90d414ad183bf2e67017b12c7
msgid ""
"The script imposes Dirichlet velocities on every boundary node equal to "
"the exact solution at the current time. This sidesteps the need for "
"periodic boundaries and isolates the spatial / temporal discretization "
"error."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/taylor_green.rst:38
#: 0a1959b0b5e5470ab935fcabeea9fc35
msgid "Solver"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/taylor_green.rst:40
#: 81985bb7b61342deb99dd2caa3e5e8a9
msgid ""
"The transient ``NavierStokesTransientAssembler`` from "
":doc:`cylinder_flow` is reused verbatim — implicit Euler in time, "
"SUPG/PSPG with adaptive :math:`\\tau` in space. The only changes are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/taylor_green.rst:45
#: a529e80b94034b219133e4402cb6cbbe
msgid "domain :math:`[0, 2\\pi]^2` instead of the cylinder channel,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/taylor_green.rst:46
#: 44b990e283e84054b2e4935600a98583
msgid "Dirichlet velocity from the exact solution rather than a parabolic inlet,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/taylor_green.rst:48
#: d2f26fa2f20144ea8a89e5b9f2a91423
msgid ""
"every step writes :math:`L^2` errors against the analytical velocity and "
"pressure to a results file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/taylor_green.rst:51
#: bd827ebbe7a84c038e8ac58d4b5523e1
msgid "examples/fluid/taylor_green/taylor_green.py (essence)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/taylor_green.rst:71
#: 6a1678355b064ee8b0f0f677c5e84910
msgid "h-convergence"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/taylor_green.rst:73
#: e427776f3645454e83cb610e59aadb51
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"The script sweeps the mesh size :math:`h = 2\\pi / n_\\text{grid}` "
"through a list of values and records the :math:`L^2` velocity and "
"pressure errors at a fixed final time. For P1-P1 elements with SUPG/PSPG "
"one expects:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/taylor_green.rst:78
#: 33fba1ccb1374e7ea1cbbd5f9a84fd73
#, python-brace-format
msgid ":math:`\\|\\mathbf{u}_h - \\mathbf{u}\\|_{L^2} = \\mathcal{O}(h^2)`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/taylor_green.rst:79
#: 537690b6521c420ca152629b76e5af3a
#, python-brace-format
msgid ":math:`\\|p_h - p\\|_{L^2} = \\mathcal{O}(h)`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/taylor_green.rst:81
#: 30ec3d64f3d84863b84001b1a41ddaea
msgid "The console output is a table:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/taylor_green.rst:92
#: 3966e0ec7fc24ad697456f29ed24741f
msgid ""
"(numbers approximate, will vary slightly with the chosen :math:`\\nu` and"
" :math:`\\Delta t`). The plot ``taylor_green_convergence.png`` shows the "
"same data on a log-log axis with reference :math:`h^2` and :math:`h^1` "
"slopes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/taylor_green.rst:97
#: 33aabd5ec46b4f16a6a3c35a9d3d2986
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"If the observed rates differ from the expected :math:`\\mathcal{O}(h^2)` "
"/ :math:`\\mathcal{O}(h)`, something in the solver is wrong — most often "
"a subtle bug in the stabilization or in the boundary-condition "
"imposition."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/taylor_green.rst:104
#: 732bbdc9d2794454b919ee725e0b3971
msgid "Mass-weighted error norm"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/taylor_green.rst:106
#: bf09b5b4f2054c9b9042a381f0e7dcea
msgid "The script computes the discrete :math:`L^2` norm via the mass matrix:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/taylor_green.rst:109
#: a29be2d4cb1a4971925f2488fa07ef17
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"\\|e_h\\|_{L^2}^2\n"
"\\;=\\;\n"
"e_h^T\\, M\\, e_h\n"
"\\;=\\;\n"
"\\sum_K \\int_K e_h^2 \\,\\mathrm{d}\\Omega,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/taylor_green.rst:117
#: ccaf8543f955417f8d670d984428ff0d
msgid ""
"assembled by :class:`~tensormesh.MassElementAssembler`. This is the right"
" norm for FEM error analysis (it integrates over the elements, weighted "
"by the basis), unlike the simple Euclidean norm of the nodal error "
"vector."
msgstr ""

